<h1>Raw Nerve</h1>

<p>This is a series of pieces on getting better at life.</p>

<ol>
<li><a href="stepback">Take a step back</a></li>
<li><a href="dweck">Believe you can change</a></li>
<li><a href="semmelweis">Look at yourself objectively</a></li>
<li><a href="dalio">Lean into the pain</a></li>
<li><a href="anders">Confront reality</a></li>
<li><a href="geremiah">Cherish mistakes</a></li>
<li><a href="nummi">Fix the machine, not the person</a></li>
</ol>

<p>The best posts are probably 2 and 4.</p>

<p>Bonus pieces:</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="optimalbias">What are the optimal biases to overcome?</a></li>
</ul>

<p>Related reading:</p>

<ul>
<li><em><a href="http://books.theinfo.org/go/B0062Q7S3S">The Flinch</a></em> (for part 4)</li>
